    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="279"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Emperor</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On the occasion of the opening this day of the cable that brings Germany in close
                    telegraphic union with the United States, I rejoice to express to your
                    excellency my gratification at the completion of this important work of peace. I
                    know that your excellency and I are of one mind in the wish and in the hope that
                    the cable connection will promote the general welfare and help in maintaining
                    and strengthening friendly relations between the two countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilhelm I. R.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
